  "buggy_files": [
    "drivers/acpi/video_detect.c"
  ],
  "buggy_functions": [
    "video_detect_dmi_table"
  ],
  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reasoning": "The Acer TravelMate 5735Z laptop is missing from the video_detect_dmi_table, which contains DMI-based quirks for backlight driver selection. Without this entry, the kernel's acpi_video_get_backlight_type() function cannot detect that this model requires native ACPI backlight control by default. Instead, it falls back to autodetection which selects intel_backlight or acer_wmi drivers, neither of which work properly for this hardware. Adding an entry to the video_detect_dmi_table that matches the system's DMI vendor (Acer) and product name (TravelMate 5735Z), with a callback to video_detect_force_native(), would force the native backlight driver to be used by default, fixing the brightness control issue."
}

